Package controller

Class modifyPartForm

java.lang.Object
controller.modifyPartForm
All Implemented Interfaces:
javafx.fxml.Initializable
public class modifyPartForm extends Object implements javafx.fxml.Initializable
This class allows to modify values of In-House and Outsourced objects of type Part and to update the ObservableList allParts in the Inventory class.

The modifyPartForm class implements the Initializable class interface. It provides control to the data flow into model objects and updates the view modifyPartForm FXML class.

Author:
Myriam Drouin-Sagar

    • onCancelModifyPart

      public void onCancelModifyPart(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent) throws IOException
      Cancels the modifyPartForm and returns to the mainForm. It displays a confirmation dialog box. If confirmed, a call to the function returnToMainScreen will redirect the user to the mainForm.
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - The event generated by the Cancel button cancelModifyPartButton when clicked by the user
      Throws:
      IOException - from the FXMLoader in the method returnToMainScreen

    • onSaveModifyPart

      public void onSaveModifyPart(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent) throws IOException
      Gets and save a new InHouse or Outsourced object's values entered by the user in the modifyPartForm and loads the mainForm.

      It updates the ObservableList allParts with the newly created instance of InHouse or Outsourced type Part by calling the updatePart method of the Inventory class.

      A call to the minMaxValid method and invValid method is made, and an error message is displayed if min or inv is not valid. It gets the machine ID value if the In-house radio button is selected. It gets the company name value if the Outsourced radio button is selected.

      NumberFormatException to catch invalid values (string in an int text field) or an empty text field. If caught, an error message is displayed.

      Parameters:
      actionEvent - The event generated by the Save button saveModifyPartButton when clicked by the user
      Throws:
      IOException - from the FXMLoader in the method returnToMainScreen
